description: Translates Guardians of The Galaxy #2.
Translates Guardians of The Galaxy: Tomorrow's Avengers #1.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #4.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #5.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #6.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #7-8.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #9.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #10.
Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #11.
name: El Juicio de Jean Grey #2

description: Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #12.
name: El Juicio de Jean Grey #4

description: Translates Guardians of the Galaxy #13.
name: El Juicio de Jean Grey #6

description: The triceratop's final show down with the raptors (?), Richard's final (almost certainly not) showdown with Alana, we find out what happened to Jasper in the prehistoric and where the name Blastosaurus came from.
name: Welcome To Freak Out City Part Six of Six

description:
ONE COMIC BOOK, THREE STORIES. WELCOME TO THE DOGHOUSE ISSUE TWO.

"BRITONS... SAXONS... WHERE THE FUCK ARE WE?"

A British Army Chinook falls out of the sky and crash lands... somewhere else. The survivors are a long long way from home - in AVALON.

"AH SHUT UP. HE DIDN'T SHOOT YOU THAT HARD"

Meet Officer Franco, an old-school cop on the beat in a New York that isn't quite the same as it used to be - in NYPD WEIRD.

"BURN IN HELL, JACK MILLER"

A blue collar repo man takes his team after white collar assholes, but things never quite go to plan for Jack Miller - in REPO DELUXE.
name: Avalon; N.Y.P.D. Weird; Repo Deluxe

description: Dungeon Quest Book Three continues the adventures of Millennium Boy, Steve, Lash and Nerdgirl as they traverse mysterious underground realms. This latest installment of the stoner D&D epic brings a whole new level of bizarre comedy, rousing adventure and ass-kicking action - all staged in front of fantastic backdrops replete with strange vegetation, ancient ruins and steam-punk imagery.
Amber races to bring The Endling into the real world as he makes his last stand in his.

The fate of the entire world is in Joshua Blacks hands, and he could not care less. When the gaze of the seraph decimates Nevada, its made very clear that time is running out. Now his archangel handlers, Michael and Samael have left Joshua in the hands of Jesus Christ himself, hoping the former messiah can talk some sense into the stubbornly reluctant teenager.

But when the temptation of the sexy succubus, Levetica causes a jealousy fueled argument with his girlfriend Tracy, Josh is just too busy dealing with his own personal high school drama, to deal with being God.
What has been going on in the other tribes of South-East Melburn? Here's your chance to find out.
Camille explains to Eric why he has been taken in by the anti-A. Wilhelm and Henry are on their way to the camp.
name: Vol. 8

description: The Miami Vice team closes in on the drug cartel that has set up shop in Miami, only to discover that they're also trafficking in prostitution. As Zito and Switek lose the suspect they've been tailing, Castillo pushes the Organized Crime Bureau team to perform an undercover raid to bring in a member of the cartel's elite clientele.

Chased by the Living and the Dead!

After arriving in Morocco to track down and stop the Nazi alchemist, Kapitan Kreatur, the Militia got into a fracas with a group of Nazi soldiers at a cafe in Casablanca. Now on the run from the local police, one of Kreatur's undead minions has spotted them.

Meet Max, the friendliest killer in the world, who also happens to be the number one elite in Zero's deadly organization... and the one Naja believes is trying to kill her. So it only makes sense that she take him out first, but to do that, she needs to find him...

"EVERYTHING IS CALCULABLE, PT. 2"As reality disassembles and reassembles, the chase goes on. And this time, Nick Fury is ready to kill. Final showdown on the dry seabed of a parted ocean!

NOTE: The full issue of ORIGINAL SIN #3 includes this Infinite comic with the purchase of that issue.
name: Everything Is Calculable, Pt. 2

volume.name: Original Sin: Secret Avengers Infinite Comic

description: Punky is in quite the pickle when the perfect adoptive parents come by Fenster Hall looking for a girl just her age. Punky can't give up on Henry, but this new couple has a yard for Brandon, good schools for Punky to go to, and they're just plain nice to boot. What kind of scheme does Punky have in store this time?!
name: The Perfect Home

description:
Nights of the Living Dead

Alexander tries to befriend a Mexican drug dealer and lure him into his trap. But is he over his head this time?
name: Nights of the Living Dead

description:
Shattered Glass Part II

After discovering her roommate has been murdered, Annabel is forced to stare down the face of her own monstrous attacker: the same one she saw in a prophetic dream. This tragedy introduces Annabel to a completely new world of psychics, ancient magic and the seemingly random events that connect them. Taken in by a group of supernatural survivors, will these new friends be her downfall, or the only people who can understand and help her overcome her curse?
name: Shattered Glass Part II

description:
Chapter 4 pt 3

After the Rebecca accident, Brad, Danny, and Seth head to a vampire party to save Jeff.
The chase is on! The Wolf is forced into a battle against an unimaginable foe to save a family, a home, a life, that shouldn't even be possible.

Wounded and on the run from murderous forces, mercenary Anne Howard seeks refuge in a remote village with ties to the "vine boy" and his mysterious past.

VINE is a new comic series in the Tarzan/Indiana Jones tradition of exotic action adventure, with an added dose of metaphysical fantasy and romance!

Sarah recalls the origins of the Dark Witch, centuries ago, as a small town is devastated by loss. In the present day, LaMontagne gets a chance at freedom thanks to the mysterious -- and powerful -- Smythe, who offers a solution to Fordyce's possession.

Dark forces are finally meeting their match in the penultimate episode of Where the Witches Lurk!

Witch Hunter agrees to help the half-breed warrior, Skiver, overthrow his father, King Mo Greenscales, before his subjects in the Lost City of the Lizardmen overrun the Earth. Finding the lost city will be an odyssey in itself, though, as it requires the assistance of immortal Aztec mystics, a sleep-deprived tugboat captain who navigates the forgotten river of dreams, and Pepper Tiger, the jungle cat!
name: Witch Hunter in The Lost City of The Lizardmen

description: Matt's aiming for a normal life, so he's dating a new co-worker from the Mystic Grill. But when a series of grisly "animal attacks" are uncovered, Damon, Elena, and Caroline follow the new girl to see if there's more to her than it seems.
name: New in Town Part 1 of 1

description:
The Whizzer Rock Rumble!

Who is Bunyan Paulson, and why is he interrupting a national park tour with his bear wrestling match?

Wait! More importantly: how the hey does a little kid expect to beat one of the Four Great Bears who stand at the very pinnacle of human/ursine wrestling?
name: The Whizzer Rock Rumble!

description: starts with the story of Whit , embroiled in a turf war with a rival gang, and ends with the story of an unusual escape from imprisonment.

Celebrities Reacting Offensively To Criminal Happenings

This #0 issue features a 7-page story of actor/agent, Jack Gallyon on a mission to retrieve a briefcase for the head of C.R.O.T.C.H., Mr. Kiernan. In order to to restore his celebrity image, Jack is sent to Libya for the job. Also, included in this issue are the page pencils, page inks, and concept artwork for the C.R.O.T.C.H. team.
name: Celebrities Reacting Offensively To Criminal Happenings

description: A brilliant scientist wakes up in a strange hotel room with a titanium briefcase shackled to his wrist and no idea how it got there. As he desperately tries to stay a step ahead of the international terrorists, CIA, and MI-6 agents chasing him across the globe, he realizes that he is the only person who can keep this mysterious briefcase from being delivered to Washington -- and thwart what could be the deadliest terrorist attack in history.
name: GN

description:
Ten years after the tragic events that shook the small town of Grey Oaks, the world has become a very different place.

Their mother is gone, their father has abandoned them, and Jessie and her younger brother, Alex, are living as outcasts from society in an isolated corner of rural Mexico.

With their only friend, an alcoholic bartender from The Last Stand tavern, and a mysterious stranger called Ron, they must locate Yaqui Indian Don Candillo to survive an impending invasion that threatens to bring their entire world to a brutal end.

These are their Changing Ways.
name: Book II

description: Isolated on the American frontier the town of Redemption casts a dark shadow. The arrival of a stranger forces long kept secrets into the light and reveals a greater threat to the town and its inhabitants. Judgement awaits the living and the dead as a forlorn group of gunfighters and settlers must fight for their lives against a primeval supernatural terror. Night approaches, and with it comes the Dark Hours.

The Great Caper of Crime

It takes the right kind of person to be a super-villain's henchman. Strong, not very smart, and willing to take orders - or a punch. Roy Murphy is that kind of guy, which is why he's employee of the month at his local henchman temp agency. But what will Roy do when he not only has to deal with Dober-Man and Beagle, the Canine Crusaders, but also with a fellow henchman and his GREAT CAPER OF CRIME? Dober-Man Volume 1 is a zany, fun, all-ages action comedy inspired by the Silver Age of comics.
name: The Great Caper of Crime

description:
Welcome to Astral

Four teens with strange mental abilities have suddenly gone into a mysterious coma. They soon realize that beyond the world of dreams lies a new world called, Astral. It's a dark world filled with harsh landscapes and evil monsters at every corner. Will they survive long enough to learn the truth... find out now.
name: Beyond the Veil

description: Antarctic Press presents a tense tale of the super-noir-tual, co-written by Justified writer VJ Boyd! In 1947, hard-boiled police detective Tom Fraley was murdered by a vicious serial killer. Now, in 2013, someone is replicating that killer's pattern. Fraley's spirit returns to hunt down the criminal and take vengeance for his own death. Collects Ghost Cop #1-3.
name: TPB

description: Solomon Hitch has battled a lot of strange enemies during his career as Halloween Man -- but now a seemingly unstoppable serial killer has a death grip on Solar City. The Invisible Man has blown into town, with murder on his mind and mad science on his agenda. Can America's favorite undead superhero outwit one of the most famous monsters of all time? Or will Solar City be forever in the thrall of the unseen terror? Halloween Man vs. the Invisible Man collects the entire critically acclaimed, award-nominated story arc.

volume.name: Halloween Man vs. the Invisible Man

description:
Bash at the Birthday

Donald Peterson has been eagerly anticipating the biggest pay-per-view event from the IWF (Incredible Wrestling Federation). It happens to coincide with his birthday. But, could the party and the show be ruined by the shenanigans of his younger brother, Derek?
name: Bash At the Birthday

description: While managing a high-class rental boutique, Rose often dreams of her own wedding. Then, one day, she has an unexpected encounter. Included with a returned wedding dress is a planner that must have been forgotten. To return the planner to its rightful owner, she goes to a famous advertising firm and there she spots the man of her dreams; his name is Duncan Burke. As soon as she catches sight of him, he owns her heart, and then everything changes. It's obvious that many women desire him. To be with him, she abandons her previous image of jeans and flats, and dyes her hair blond, all to transform herself into a beautiful princess.
name: Vol. 1

description: Our lives are just the surface of vast subliminal realities. The events that take place on the Earth are the result of deep and powerful occult forces invisible for our material eyes. A series of experiences will force Alex White to face a strong enemy in the inner spaces. That will not only put to test his whole inner development so far but is going to threaten his life as well.
name: The Growth of Light Within

description: Journalist Allison Breaking gets more than she bargained for when she's hired to write the memoirs of the rich and eccentric Burma, who turns out to be a cat! Burma isn't like other cats, though-and Allison will be shocked to find out how he's spent his nine lives! From writer Paul Tobin (Bandette, Colder) and artist Benjamin Dewey (The Tragedy Series) comes the story of a very remarkable cat.
name: Chapter One

description:
Birdheads

Joyce Sunn wants to quit her dead-end job as a superhero sidekick named Thrasher. In this issue, she discovers a mystery, engages in a verbal confrontation with her arch nemesis in flashback, and falls down the rabbit hole that is the history of her mentor, the Jackdaw.
name: Birdheads

description: Having brought the world of Judge Dredd crashing down, Dredd co-creator John Wagner leads a team of 2000 ADs best writers and artists in the incredible follow-up to the critically acclaimed Judge Dredd: Day of Chaos collections. The survivors of the Chaos Bug viral attack that killed 350 million citizens must struggle on as a hugely depleted Justice Department desperately tries to maintain control in sectors now reduced to nothing but graveyards where looting is rife and crime is rampant. From high-action gun battles to enthralling political intrigue it contains incredible, challenging writing from John Wagner (History of Violence), Rob Williams (The Royals), and Michael Carroll (Jennifer Blood) and stunning full-colour artwork from Laurence Campbell (BPRD), Trevor Hairsine (Cla$$war), James Harren (BPRD), Dave Taylor (Batman & Superman: Worlds Finest), Inaki Miranda and Eva De La Cruz (Fables: Fairest 2), Andrew Currie (Smax), and PJ Holden (Department of Monsterology).
name: TPB

volume.name: Judge Dredd: Day of Chaos: Fallout

description: New collection for North America: From state-of-the-art sex-bots to the hugely-popular sex championships, for enough credits Mega-City Ones citizens can indulge in their wildest, erotic desires. But some people cant help themselves and break the law when looking for lust in all the wrong places! This collection of lascivious law-breaking tales features work from some of 2000 ADs greatest talent, including Judge Dredd creators John Wagner and Carlos Ezquerra, Alan Grant (Batman), Greg Staples (Sinister Dexter), Ian Gibson (The Ballad of Halo Jones) and Simon Bisley (Hellblazer) amongst others.
name: TPB

description:
The gears of justice roll on in a new graphic novel by best-selling author Mark (Doc Savage, Outlanders) Ellis, David (Batman/Superman, Infinity, Inc,) Enebral and Ivan (Legend of Isis) Barriga.

The Justice Machine fought to destroy tyranny on two worlds--but nearly twenty years ago they vanished, never to be seen again.

Until now! The Machine's explosive return plunges them into a nightmarish landscape of two realities warring for dominion! The team races to thwart a dark destiny awaiting all humanity if they fail to stop an unspeakable evil from gaining a foothold to the future!

Painted front and back covers by Jeff Slemons!

Special features include a history of the Justice Machine with artwork by Adam Hughes, Darryl Banks, Robert Castro and Jack Kirby!
name: GN

volume.name: The Justice Machine: Object of Power

description:
The Man, The Myth, The Amulet? Legendary star of the small and silver screen, ADAM WEST has his career youth-enized in this hip, whimsical, trans-dimensional epic of an adventure. When a mysterious fan delivers an exotic amulet to Mr. West's doorstep, he is Dorothy-fied on an odyssey that will change his career, his love life, and inadvertently make him the man that saves the universe!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
ACover AMatt Bellisle1
BCover BRussell DautermanMissing
CCover CLipeMissing

From an ethereal creation to a predestined end, a secret history of the world has existed with supernatural forces controlling the fate of mankind. What would begin as a fight over beliefs, would spillover and forever alter the course of human history. A comprehensive look at how the ultimate battle between good and evil began and important clues to its end.
name: Mythos

description:
Megumi is an all-star athlete, but she's a failure when it comes to physics class. And she can't concentrate on her tennis matches when she's worried about the questions she missed on the big test! Luckily for her, she befriends Ryota, a patient physics geek who uses real-world examples to help her understand classical mechanics-and improve her tennis game in the process!

In The Manga Guide to Physics, you'll follow alongside Megumi as she learns about the physics of everyday objects like roller skates, slingshots, braking cars, and tennis serves. In no time, you'll master tough concepts like momentum and impulse, parabolic motion, and the relationship between force, mass, and acceleration.

After many years, Karissa has finally returned to the Caramel kingdom to secure her dream job of managing a boardinghouse. Upon her arrival, she meets the son of a major noble family. This very man was her first love and had cruelly rejected her affection. Painful emotions, unhealed by time, run wild in her heart. As she's reeling from this encounter, she learns something even more unsettling: he's the owner of the boardinghouse that she's been hired to run.
name: Vol. 1

description: Sometimes all it takes to become a hero is an unfortunate incident and a single split second decision. Behold the origin of Midnight Tiger!

Long demanded by fans this is a brand new edition of the second volume of futuristic swashbuckling adventurer Nikolai Dante for the UK and Ireland, with a brand new cover by co-creator Simon Fraser! Having discovered his heritage and bio-bonded with the awesome Weapons Crest, Dante is getting to know his newfound family a little better. Ordered to act as his father Dmitris agent, Nikolai accompanies his siblings on a tour of family duty spying, murder and intrigue. But does he have what it takes to be a true Romanov? Written by Robbie Morrison (The Authority), with art by Charlie Adlard (The Walking Dead), Andy Clarke (Batman & Robin) and Simon Fraser (Judge Dredd), this second collection in the ongoing chronicles of Nikolai Dante will transport you to a world of intrigue, romance and adventure!
name: TPB

description:
Chiyuki Amamiya works as a public prosecutor at the western branch of the Tokyo district public prosecutor's office. One day, two men transfer to Amamiya's office. One of them is Yoshitaka Morooka, the progeny of a long line of merchants. The other is Masachika Katori, the man they used to call the home office prince before he fell from grace! Amamiya has just broken up with his boyfriend and, starving for some skin-to-skin contact, ends up sleeping with Katori after a night of drinking...

Chapter Titles

  • File.1: Deceitful Men
  • File.2: What's Your Sin
  • File.3: Pride
  • File.4: Their Circumstances
  • File.4.5
name: Vol. 1

description: Rumor 1: The Legend of the Hawk-Ai! Face front, true believers, as an alternate origins story of Princess Ai unfolds! Silver-age superhero antics abound!
name: Rumor 1: The Legend of the Hawk-Ai!

volume.name: Princess Ai: Rumors From the Other Side

description:
Welcome to Jacinto & Lennox Retrievals, the best damn thieves on the planet. From Fort Knox to Wonderland, if you want it they'll get it, no questions. For a price, of course.

Rough week for J & L. Monday: The Egg of First Light is stolen. Tuesday: J&L are hired to retrieve it. By Thursday alien magic, super assassins, and Armageddon stand between them and their payday. Friday: Ka-Boom?!
In 2007, Ryan was thrown from a train. He totally deserved it. The true story of a cross-country standoff between an army of police officers and one dumb foreigner.

Due to problems at home regarding his future, Sora runs away to live with Tetsuya. During this time they confirm that their feelings for each other are mutual, and it naturally progresses further. But soon they find out that love isn't the only thing they'll need to keep their relationship going. How will these two growing young adults maintain their increasingly difficult relationship... and figure out their own unclear futures?
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Second Night of A Thousand Nights

description: Sentinels is the story of a second generation superhero team whose parents disappeared when they were young. As they step into their new roles as heroes and struggle to take charge of their lives, they get pulled into the mystery of what happened to the first generation.

Young Lanna is the daughter of the world's foremost multimillionaire, and because of that fact, she finds that all of the men who approach her are disgusting. She just wants to go somewhere where nobody knows who she is, and to finally meet somebody who will love her for her, not for her father's wealth. Enter Arash, an exchange student come to study at a British university. with purple eyes and a mysterious appearance, she believes that he's her destined love. However, it turns out that he's actually a prince from a desert country. Since their worlds are so different he tries to stop seeing her, but finds that he cannot free himself of his feelings for her. War arises in his homeland and he's called back. with no time left, they spend one last night together. "Love me," she says to him. But the next morning he leaves in a cold and distant manner! What has happened?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Snipe, originally released as a book object in a very limited edition of 100, consists of two discrete stories. Snipe I follows a wildlife photographer lost in the woods while memories of his previous night's fever dream gradually surface. Snipe II is a highly detailed and possibly fictionalized account of the life and career WWII's most celebrated sniper, Finland's Simo Hyh. Where these stories intersect is in the territory of memory and inaccuracy, myth-building and psychosis.

This project is another point on the Immonens' trajectory of continually exploring comics and experimental storytelling.

Inspired by the sci-fi cult films of the 1950's comes a brand new space-tastic adventure. A bunch of scientists decide to take flight to the moon and discover a race of alien women ruled by a fierce and sadistic queen.
name: TPB

description:
For the first time ever, a visual presentation of the much-discussed, unrevised, unadulterated version of Harlan Ellison's award-winning Star Trek teleplay script, 'The City on the Edge of Forever!' This Hugo- and Writer's Guild of America Award-winning teleplay has been much discussed for decades but only here can you see the story as Mr. Ellison originally intended!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverJuan Ortiz1
SubSubscription CoverPaul Shipper3
2ndSecond Printing CoverJuan Ortiz2

Note: The digital edition (6/4/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

volume.name: Star Trek: Harlan Ellison's Original The City On the Edge of Forever Teleplay

description:
In the midst of the Depression, the Dust Bowl settles on the Midwest, turning many farms into useless expanses of loose dust. For the farmers struggling to hold onto their livelihoods and heritage, it's a fruitless struggle on a dying land.

One such farmer, Vernon, struggles to keep the farm passed down through his family for generations alive. Then he discovers a grotesque stalk in his cornfield. Despite crops failing around it, this stalk thrives and grows larger - by feasting on blood.

When his wife becomes gravely ill, Vernon accidentally ignites a series of events that transform his life - and his land - forever...

Tribes, Part 1

Still reeling from the death of his wife, Marc and the rest of the team make important choices about the future.
name: Tribes, Part 1

description: A mysterious figure has begun killing every living being in their sleep. You arise to the sounds of knocking at your door followed by whispers of a countdown from 5 to 1. The figure floats into your doorway and drains your blood using tubes that feed and replenish his own evil body. The figure wears a welder's mask and a glowing clock. The world population is terrified as governments across the globe try to track down this dark entity to find out what it wants. Agent Mac Loomis is dispatched to protect his own sister Rachael from this dark figure that seems particularly interested in tormenting her. Could this be the end of the world? Who is this dark figure? Who is it?...Doomsday!
name: GN

description:
The rise of Christianity amongst the north-men has frustrated Odin, Father of the Norse Gods. Out of jealousy and anger, he has transformed three of his most loyal berserkers into unstoppable beasts, and set them loose upon his traitorous followers.

Thor, God of Thunder, takes it upon himself to challenge his father's madness by aiding a loyal warrior of his own: the viking Tyr. Along with the help of a witch and two strangers, Tyr must face the wolves and realize his own destiny.

This is the story of mankind clawing for survival, of mankind on the edge. The world outside has grown unkind, the view of it limited, talk of it forbidden. But there are always those who hope, who dream. These are the dangerous people, the residents who infect others with their optimism. Their punishment is simple. They are given the very thing they profess to want: They are allowed outside.

It all begins here! Hugh Howey's bestselling Wool makes the leap into comics, with mysteries and thrills for new fans and surprises for the already faithful. In issue #1 of 6: The Silo is explored, and a lie is revealed.

Collects strips that appeared from November 8, 2010 to January 23, 2012 of the Asian American office romance webcomic Yellow Peril. Passed up for promotion for refusing to conform to corporate culture, graphic designer Kane Hongo must learn to play the game in the cubicle jungle of Pedanticorp. Helping him navigate the contrived ways of the corporate drone is his two cohorts, Bodie Guy and Ally Peth.

Kane, Bodie, and Ally have long suffered at the hands of their pedantic boss, Steve. Their disgruntled commiserations have evolved into plans to strike out on their own. Will they finally be able to break free from their corporate shackles?
name: Volume 2

volume.name: The Client Is Always: A Yellow Peril Collection

description: ZippyCakes and SnotMuffin in a one-shot adventure! Also featuring a Villains 'Who's Who' in the ZippyCakes & SnotMuffin universe! A must have for fans, and a must read for the curious!

John Constantine heads toward a final showdown with a revenge-crazed Satan during a raging race riot! While trying to save his remaining friends, Constantine has a final reunion with his lost love Kit. Collects HELLBLAZER #78-83 plus HEARTLAND #1.

Unlike the solicit says, this collection collects issues #72-83 and Heartland.
name: Vol. 8

volume.name: Hellblazer: Rake at the Gates of Hell
Baka to Test to Shoukanjuu Ja

description: This comical collection of of Jewish comedian portraiture is a sequel to 2006's wildly successful Old Jewish Comedians, which earned Friedman raves from Jerry Lewis, Howard Stern, The Believer,Entertainment Weekly and many more, and earned Friedman his own roast at New York's legendary Friar's Club. This all-new collection includes the famous (Woody Allen, Carl Reiner, Joan Rivers, Mel Brooks, Soupy Sales, etc.), the not-so-famous (Jerry Stiller, Zeppo & Gummo Marx, Larry Storch, Zero Mostel, etc.) and the largely unknown (Molly Picon, Herbie Faye, Jan Milton, etc.). The Reuben Award-winning Friedman, one of the great caricaturists of his age, presents a thorough visual history of the 20th Century's greatest Borscht-Belt comedians.
name: GN
